  "notes": "Standard Modern Greek (Demotic). 5-vowel system despite many graphemic representations. Digraphs ⟨μπ⟩, ⟨ντ⟩, ⟨γκ⟩ represent voiced stops, with prenasalisation medially. PALATALIZATION: γ/κ/χ palatalize before front vowels (e/i/η/ι/υ): γ→[ʝ], κ→[c], χ→[ç]. ΑΥ/ΕΥ: [av]/[ev] before voiced sounds; [af]/[ef] before voiceless. Σ: [z] before voiced consonants (σβ, σγ, σδ, etc.). Sources: Arvaniti (2007), Holton et al. (2004), Setatos (1974).",
  "quality": "research",
